1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Science reveals how anchoring bias controls your choices more than you think.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:11,200
Anchoring bias happens when we rely too heavily on the first piece of information we receive.

3
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:14,800
Imagine seeing a $1,000 TV, then a $500 one.

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,600
That $500 looks like a steal, right?

5
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:23,200
Studies show people are more likely to buy when they're anchored to higher prices.

6
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:30,400
Being aware of this bias can help you make smarter choices, not just in shopping, but in life.

7
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:33,200
Want to learn more about your mind?

8
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,800
Hit that follow button!
